HEADWORD: Anthological
<hw>An`tho*log"ic*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining
to anthology; consisting of beautiful extracts from different authors,
especially the poets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He published a geographical and <qex>anthological</qex>
description of all empires and kingdoms . . . in this terrestrial
globe.</q> <rj><qau>Wood.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anthologist</ent>⟦br⟧
